EASTERN EQUINE ENCEPHALITIS - USA (MASSACHUSETTS)
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Tue, 2 Sep 1997 09:51:32 -0400
From: George Robertson <grobertson@mail.ncifcrf.gov>
The first [human] illness due to eastern equine encephalitis [EEE] virus this
year in Massachusetts was reported by state health officials over the
weekend. According to the Associated Press, a 69-year-old man from
Plainville, Massachusetts is critically ill after infection with the virus.
The case was reported approximately three weeks after the virus was detected
in eastern and southeastern Massachusetts, prompting a warning at that time
from the Massachusetts of Public Health that persons living in those areas
should take protective precautions.
---
